Scenario:
You are developing a graphic design tool where users frequently reuse predefined colors. Creating a new color object from scratch every time is inefficient if a similar object already exists.

Requirements:

Prototype: An abstract Color class (or interface) that implements a cloning mechanism.

Concrete Prototypes: BlackColor and BlueColor which provide their own cloning logic.

Prototype Registry: ColorStore that caches predefined color objects and provides clones upon request.

Goal: Specify the kinds of objects to create using a prototypical instance, and create new objects by copying this prototype. This is particularly useful when the cost of creating a new object is more expensive than cloning an existing one.